 * `maxLength` number (optional) - Maximum number of UTF-16 code units to return
   in `html`. Must be between `1` and `1000000`. Default is `100000`.
+* `inlineStyles` boolean (optional) - Whether to copy each element's computed
+  style into its `style` attribute in the returned `html`. Default is `false`.
 
-This object configures the raw HTML snapshot returned by
+This object configures the HTML snapshot returned by
 `webContents.getFocusedEditableText()` and `webContents.watchFocusedEditableText()`.
 The top-level `maxLength` option limits `text`; `html.maxLength` only limits
 `html`.
+By default, `html` is the focused contenteditable host's raw `innerHTML`.
+When `inlineStyles` is `true`, Electron returns a cloned HTML snapshot with
+computed styles inlined on each element. This can make class-based styling
+portable, but it can also produce much larger HTML.
